<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-153-071 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 758 351</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  May 17 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>VA's EDP wings clipped in buying restriction. (VeteranAdministration's Electronic Data Processing)</TITLE><AUTHOR>McCormick, John.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Topic:     PolicyComputer SystemsElectronic Data ProcessingGovernment ContractsGovernment Funding.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>VA'S EDP WINGS CLIPPED IN BUYING RESTRICTION 05/17/91 WASHINGTON, D.C.,andO;U.S.A., 1991 MAY 17 (NB) -- The General Services Administration has cut theVeterans Affairs Department's ability to purchase computer equipment withoutGSA oversight by 75 percent from $10 million to only $2.5 million.andM;Back in 1986 the GSA had started allowing the VA to purchase computer systemsvalued at up to $10 million without approval of the government's mainpurchasing watchdog but a recent reevaluation has caused the GSA to rescindmost of that independence because of misuse of the funds.andM;The new cap means that the GSA must individually approve all purchasesinvolving more than $2.5 million in EDP or electronic data processingequipment.andM;(John McCormick/19910517)</TEXT></DOC>